WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.090 --> 00:00:02.349
From the Service Operations Workspace homepage,

1
00:00:02.559 --> 00:00:04.809
tasks assigned to your group are available under

2
00:00:05.130 --> 00:00:06.269
Your Team's Work.

3
00:00:07.059 --> 00:00:09.920
Use the "Catalog tasks assigned to your group" widget

4
00:00:10.090 --> 00:00:11.739
to open a list of assigned work.

5
00:00:13.829 --> 00:00:15.220
Selecting a task opens the record.

6
00:00:16.110 --> 00:00:19.469
The task form includes all the information needed to complete the work,

7
00:00:20.219 --> 00:00:21.690
including who the request is for

8
00:00:21.829 --> 00:00:23.899
and the requested item or service.

9
00:00:24.149 --> 00:00:26.270
The information submitted with the request is

10
00:00:26.270 --> 00:00:28.579
populated directly onto the task form,

11
00:00:28.920 --> 00:00:32.130
so everything needed to begin work is available in one place.

12
00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:35.520
Attachments provided with the request are available in the activity stream,

13
00:00:35.880 --> 00:00:38.750
along with any updates or communication related to the task.

14
00:00:39.849 --> 00:00:42.990
The related Requested Item record can be opened in a new tab

15
00:00:43.250 --> 00:00:44.930
if additional context is needed.

16
00:00:47.389 --> 00:00:49.950
Tasks are assigned to individuals when work begins.

17
00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:51.549
To take ownership of the task,

18
00:00:51.759 --> 00:00:53.880
enter your name in the Assigned To field.

19
00:00:56.340 --> 00:00:59.060
Then update the State to "Work in progress".

20
00:01:00.689 --> 00:01:01.869
Then save your changes.

21
00:01:02.169 --> 00:01:02.720
From here,

22
00:01:02.930 --> 00:01:05.370
the task can be worked and updated through to completion.
